title: The Nude Restaurant [1967 - USA] Andy Warhol
description:
The Nude Restaurant (1967 - USA)

Underground / Experimental / Semi-Documentary

director . . . . Andy Warhol
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0062055/


Andy Warhol shot two versions of The Nude Restaurant on the same day in October 1967 at the Mad Hatter restaurant. The original concept was to edit both versions into one final product. One version contained footage of an all-nude, all-male cast and was never released publicly as an independent film. The other version, with the actors and Viva wearing G-strings, was shown at the Hudson Theater on West 44th Street as one of Warhol's series of sexploitation films, or nudies as he liked to call them.
